data.title: Stations and connections with the Barcelona R11 train line
data.meta_description: Barcelona R11 train line - Stations, connections and route of Barcelona's R11 train line, between Catalonia and the Pyrénées Orientales.
data.text:
Access by R11 train line

Barcelona Casa Batllo

With large number of elements reminding human skeleton, the Casa Batllo, one of the many Antoni Gaudi must-see monuments in Barcelona, is very easily remarkable in the heart of the Passeig de Gracia.

Barcelona Casa Batllo little preview

Barcelona Casa Batllo pass online

Casa Milà / Pedrera

Casa Milà, also known as Pedrera, which means stone quarry, is a huge house with the peculiarity of having no right angles. It also forms part of Antoni Gaudi's unmissable Unesco World Heritage monuments.

Little preview of your next visit

Book your tickets online

Casa Amatller

Adjacent to Casa Batllo, Casa Amatller is a building converted into a house by the architect Josep Puig i Cadafalch at the request of the famous chocolate maker Antoni Amatller.

Casa Amatller pass online

Little preview of your next visit

Passeig de Gracia

The Paseo de Gracia (Passeig de Gracia), Barcelona's fashion boulevard where monuments, exceptional architecture, restaurants and boutiques of famous brands such as Hermés, Chanel or Diesel share the 1.5 kilometres that connect Plaça Catalunya to the Gracia district.

Quick visit of the Passeig de Gracia

Rambla Cataluña

Littered with shops, restaurants and terraces, the Rambla Catalunya is a pleasant stroll between Avenida Diagonal and Plaça Catalunya.

Barcelona Rambla Cataluña quick trip

Plaza Cataluña

As a very important intersection of the city, and a rallying point served by a large number of transports, Plaça Catalunya is one of the most recommended meeting points to get to the centre of Barcelona, where the pigeons have established their headquarters.

More about Plaça Catalunya in Barcelona

Espanya Industrial park

Built in 1985 on the foundations of a textile factory, the architect Luis Peña Ganchegi represented water, earth and fire around the chimneys of the old factory. The Espanya Industrial Park groups together a wide variety of bird species around an artificial lake.

where are the most beautiful parks in Barcelona

Sants train station

Short, medium and long distances, Sants train station in itself brings a very large number of destinations together, including the Costa Brava, the Costa Dorada, Andalusia and the Port Aventura park. Sants station also provides a line that gives access to Barcelona airport.
